sentence: Among the underlying components of the Russell 3000 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in JPMorgan Chase & Co (Symbol: JPM), where a total of 71,422 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 7.1 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 49.4% of JPM's average daily trading volume over the past month of 14.5 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $104 strike put option expiring July 06, 2018 , with 7,319 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 731,900 underlying shares of JPM.

Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM) saw options trading volume of 26,947 contracts, representing approximately 2.7 million underlying shares or approximately 48.2% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 5.6 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $140 strike call option expiring July 06, 2018 , with 2,339 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 233,900 underlying shares of CRM.

Below is a chart showing CRM's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $140 strike highlighted in orange:

And Noodles & Co (Symbol: NDLS) saw options trading volume of 1,613 contracts, representing approximately 161,300 underlying shares or approximately 47.5% of NDLS's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 339,345 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $15 strike call option expiring July 20, 2018 , with 558 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 55,800 underlying shares of NDLS.
